cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.LG

The paper deals with regular languages and automata, which are fundamental topics in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also involves algorithms for sorting and minimizing automata, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM). The use of co-lexicographic ordering and Myhill-Nerode equivalence suggests connections to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
